SCENARIO A: Re-Injury During PT (Week 8)
💔 Tyler doing resistance band work, feels POP in shoulder

Emergency visit to Dr. Bradley:

🏥 MRI Results: Small tear in rotator cuff (different area)

🏥 Dr. Bradley: "This is a new injury, not the labrum. Good news: smaller. Bad news: another surgery."

Options:

Second surgery (adds 3 months to recovery)
Conservative treatment (risky, might not hold)
💔 Tyler chooses: Surgery again

Creative Adjustment:

Extend storyline
Maybe Tyler doesn't return for 8-9 months instead
Could write in "complications" on TV to explain delay
SCENARIO B: Infection at Surgical Site (Week 2)
💔 Tyler develops fever, shoulder red and swollen

Hospital admission:

Infection in surgical site
Requires antibiotics, possible washout surgery
Adds 2-4 weeks to immobilization phase
Delays PT start
Creative Impact:

Minimal (already written off TV)
Could affect morale/mental health
SCENARIO C: Chronic Pain After "Full Clearance"
💔 Tyler cleared medically, but shoulder aches constantly during training

Options:

Push through (risky, could lead to re-injury)
Additional PT/strengthening (delays return)
Pain management (cortisone shots, etc.)
Retire (if truly unable to perform)
Reality: Some wrestlers never return to 100% after major injuries. They learn to work around limitations.

